---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: About WPCNA
metaDescription: Learn what WPCNA is and how it helps connect neighborhoods across White Plains.
---
{% from "components/macros.njk" import resourceCard %}

<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>About WPCNA</h1>
    <p>WPCNA connects neighborhood associations and helps residents follow civic life across White Plains.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="about-grid">
      <article class="about-copy">
        <h2>What WPCNA does</h2>
        <p>The White Plains Council of Neighborhood Associations brings neighborhood associations together, shares civic information, and gives residents a place to follow citywide issues through a neighborhood lens.</p>
        <blockquote class="mission-quote">WPCNA works to enhance quality of life in White Plains neighborhoods by sharing information, encouraging local action, and advising public officials.</blockquote>

        <h2>How residents use this site</h2>
        <p>Use this site to find neighborhood-relevant events, neighborhood profiles, WPCNA agendas, meeting materials, and ways to submit community-serving updates.</p>
        <p>Questions about WPCNA, neighborhood associations, or site content can go through the contact form.</p>
      </article>

      <div>
        <figure class="about-photo">
          <img src="{{ site.aboutImage | withPrefix }}" alt="{{ site.aboutImageAlt }}" loading="lazy">
        </figure>

        <div class="sidebar-card" id="contact-form">
          <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
          <h3>Get in touch</h3>
          <p>Send questions, corrections, or neighborhood news.</p>
          <form class="contact-form" action="{{ site.contactFormAction }}" method="POST">
            <input type="hidden" name="_subject" value="{{ site.contactFormSubject }}">
            <input type="hidden" name="_captcha" value="false">
            <input type="hidden" name="_template" value="table">

            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="contact-name">Name</label>
              <input id="contact-name" name="name" type="text" autocomplete="name" required>
            </div>

            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="contact-email">Email</label>
              <input id="contact-email" name="email" type="email" autocomplete="email" required>
            </div>

            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="contact-subject">Subject</label>
              <input id="contact-subject" name="topic" type="text" required>
            </div>

            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="contact-message">Message</label>
              <textarea id="contact-message" name="message" rows="6" required></textarea>
            </div>

            <button class="btn btn-primary btn-block" type="submit">Send message</button>
          </form>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-card" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
          <p class="eyebrow">Leadership</p>
          <h3>Archived officer list</h3>
          <p>Until a current roster is reposted, the archived 2018 WPCNA site listed these officers:</p>
          <ul class="plain-list">
            <li><strong>Co-Presidents:</strong> Bill Brady and Andrew Custodio</li>
            <li><strong>Vice Presidents:</strong> Ron Palmer and Christopher Price</li>
            <li><strong>Treasurer:</strong> Tom Osbeck</li>
            <li><strong>Recording Secretary:</strong> Ruthmarie Hicks</li>
            <li><strong>Corresponding Secretary:</strong> Louis Bruno</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-card" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
          <p class="eyebrow">How WPCNA works</p>
          <h3>By-laws and committees</h3>
          <p>The archived WPCNA site also pointed residents to the council's by-laws and committee work. Those pieces help give neighborhood associations a structure for sharing information, tracking issues, and taking on citywide topics together.</p>
          <p>If you need help finding governance materials or want to ask how WPCNA is organized, use the contact form and the council can point you in the right direction.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
